{
  "stem": "25591.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one of my great joys was working with him in the Congress as a colleague.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I very much hope at least some of my grandchildren will go into public service.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I have 17.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that's a difficult one because I first learned about American government, apart from the university courses, from my friend in Alaska who was a-- who was and is a very political animal.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I had an excellent sort of private tutor about American government.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My wife and I got married in 1950, and I remember that I was very active as a volunteer in a Congressional race in 1950 for the Democratic candidate whose name was Harold Taggart, and who lost the race.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And 30 years later, I won that seat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then in 1952, I organized what we called at that time the Stevenson-Sparkman Democratic Club in my town.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was its first president.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I worked for Stevenson.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I worked very hard with Stevenson.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In-- in '56 I worked very hard with Stevenson on his second campaign.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I worked very hard with Senator Alan Cranston in California, with Governor Pat Brown.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I have been involved with politics certainly since the early '50s.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then when our older daughter started elementary school, the path to her school I deemed very unsafe because there were cars going very near it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went down to the school board, and I proposed that they move this path where these adorable little six-year-old boys and girls were walking about 20 feet inside so they will be far from the cars.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was treated very badly by the school board, and they don't-- they told me to get lost.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I ran for the school board, and I won.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
